title: Kazakhstan, Kyrgyzstan, Oman delegates arrive Islamabad for special moot
content:
ISLAMABAD, Dec 18 (APP):The delegates of Kazakhstan, Kyrgyzstan and Oman have arrived in Islamabad on Saturday to attend 17th extraordinary session of OIC Council of Foreign Ministers.
The special moot of Organization of Islamic Cooperation (OIC) is scheduled to take place in the Federal Capital on Sunday to discuss humanitarian situation in Afghanistan.
Pakistan Ambassador to Vienna Aftab Ahmad Khokher received Deputy Foreign Ministers of Kazakhstan and Kyrgyzstan Nuryshev Shakhrat and Aibek Artykbaev, and Foreign Secretary of Oman Al Sheikh Khalifa Bin Ali AlHarthi.
